ZeroC Ice DEB Distribution
==========================

The ZeroC Ice DEB distribution includes the following packages.

Currently, the distribution supports Ubuntu 24.04 and Debian 12, for both amd64 and arm64 architectures.

DEB Package              Description
-----------------------  ---------------------------------------------------------------
zeroc-dsnode             DataStorm server
zeroc-glacier2           Glacier2 service
zeroc-ice-compilers      Slice compilers, such as slice2cpp, slice2java, and slice2py
zeroc-ice-slice          Slice definition files
zeroc-ice-utils          Utilities for administering an Ice installation
zeroc-icebox             IceBox server for C++
zeroc-icebridge          IceBridge service
zeroc-icegrid            IceGrid service
libzeroc-ice-dev         C++ headers and symlinks to Ice C++ runtime libraries
libzeroc-ice3.8-c++      Ice for C++ runtime libraries (includes plug-ins, DataStorm and client libraries for Ice services)
libzeroc-icestorm3.8     IceStorm service
php-zeroc-ice            Ice for PHP
python3-zeroc-ice        Ice for Python [1]

[1] Not available on Debian 12, which does not include Python 3.12+ â€” a requirement for Ice for Python.

For more information, visit:

- ZeroC website: https://zeroc.com
- Ice GitHub repository: https://github.com/zeroc-ice/ice
- Ice Sample Programs: https://github.com/zeroc-ice/ice-demos
